I can't stand someone right in front of me arguing that every woman who has a child needs to feed and raise it. Through his argument to oppose abortion, he wanted for me to push for a ban on prescription contraceptives and accept food shortages and crime spikes because we didn't have enough people being born from mothers getting pregnant because of contraceptive medication.

The Republican work requirements for Medicare are proof that the individual mandates will show benefits. The reason why the ACA was fraught with cost-containment issues is because, while covering the 9% of uninsured residents (20% of those uninsured are impoverished prisoners) that were in the system at the beginning of the year, running through the Medicaid expansion and population, the expectations for cost-containment were utilizing older and sicker people not covered by exchange plans so that the expected average HSA contribution of $2,800 to the full population in the ACA would be $250 and offset the cost of expanding Medicaid and exchange subsidized premiums.

The Republican perspective on the Republican attacks on the ACA are that there are two distinctly separate populations that were being ignored by liberals in the equation.
